---
title: "Scattering of Light by Free Electrons as a Test of Quantum Theory"
author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
year: 1991
abstract: >
  Schrödinger and Heisenberg gave two very different views about the
  physical meaning of an electron wave function. We argue that
  Schrödinger's view may have been dismissed prematurely through failure
  to appreciate the stabilizing effects of forces due to Zitterbewegung,
  and suggest experiments now feasible which might decide the issue.
---
