- Removed extraneous non-body metadata footnote at the end (`[^1]: Presented at the Workshop...`), which was orphaned.
- Added one missing blank line between two reference entries (`Dyson` and `Heisenberg`) for cleaner rendering.

Self-check completed:
- Paragraph boundaries intended as separate prose paragraphs are blank-line separated.
- All in-text equation references to `(1), (7), (11), (13), (15), (23), (36), (39), (40)` now resolve to display equations with visible tags.
- No paper meaning/math content was changed; only structure/formatting/tagging.
